message.content: A 'Sympetrum obtrusum' is a species of dragonfly that belongs to the family of Libellulidae. It is commonly known as the 'Long Skimmer' or 'Marsh Skimmer'. The length of its body ranges from 30-38 millimeters. It has a bright red body with black markings on its wings and abdomen. The males have a more vibrant color than females. 'Sympetrum obtrusum' can be found near still or slow-moving water bodies such as ponds, lakes, and marshes. It is a relatively common species of dragonfly that is found throughout many parts of the world. It has a long and narrow body with its wings held out flat when at rest, and it is a fast and skillful flier.
